  "summary": "metrics-pipeline-d8k2 ships postinstall beacon that exfiltrates host info and environment data",
  "details": "On install, package.json runs `postinstall: node run.js`, which executes bundled beacon scripts (beacon28.js, beacon_linux.js). These scripts collect host identifiers via `os.hostname()`, `os.platform()`, and `process.platform`, read `process.env`, invoke `child_process.exec` to run system commands, and transmit the collected data over the network via `http.request`/`https.request` and `fetch`. The behavior fires automatically on `npm install` with no consumer interaction. The package's name (random suffix `-d8k2`, generic 'metrics-pipeline' label) and shipped beacon files are inconsistent with any documented legitimate purpose.",
